AIM:
To design an interactive feedback form using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript that validates user inputs on keypress, highlights form fields on mouse hover,
and displays a confirmation message when the submit button is double-clicked.

PROCEDURE:
Create an HTML feedback form with fields:
 .Name
 .Email
 .Feedback message
Use CSS to style input fields and add hover effects.
Write JavaScript functions for:
 .Keypress validation (allow only letters for name, valid email characters)
 .Dynamic field highlighting on mouseover
 .Double-click event handling for submit confirmation
Attach JavaScript events:
 .onkeypress for live validation
 .onmouseover & onmouseout for highlighting
 .ondblclick for confirming submission
Test the form for validation, hover effects, and double-click submission confirmation.

code:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Interactive Feedback Form</title>
<style>
body { font-family: Arial; background: #f4f4f4; }
.container {
    width: 350px; background: white; padding: 20px;
    margin: 50px auto; border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px #999;
}
input, textarea {
    width: 100%; padding: 8px; margin: 10px 0;
    border: 2px solid #ccc; border-radius: 5px;
}
input:hover, textarea:hover {
    border-color: #007bff;
    background: #eef6ff;
}
button {
    width: 100%; padding: 10px; background: #007bff;
    color: white; font-size: 16px; border: none;
    border-radius: 5px; cursor: pointer;
}
button:hover { background: #0056b3; }
</style>

<script>
// Validate name (only letters)
function validateName(e) {
    let ch = String.fromCharCode(e.keyCode);
    if (!/[a-zA-Z ]/.test(ch)) {
        alert("Only letters allowed in Name!");
        return false;
    }
}

// Validate email characters
function validateEmail(e) {
    let ch = String.fromCharCode(e.keyCode);
    if (!/[a-zA-Z0-9@._]/.test(ch)) {
        alert("Invalid character for Email!");
        return false;
    }
}

// Double click submit confirmation
function confirmSubmit() {
    alert("Feedback submitted successfully!");
}
</script>
</head>

<body>
<div class="container">
    <h2>Feedback Form</h2>

    <label>Name:</label>
    <input type="text" id="name" onkeypress="return validateName(event)">

    <label>Email:</label>
    <input type="text" id="email" onkeypress="return validateEmail(event)">

    <label>Feedback:</label>
    <textarea id="fb" rows="4"></textarea>

    <button ondblclick="confirmSubmit()">Submit</button>
</div>
</body>
</html>

RESULT

Thus, an interactive web-based feedback form was successfully created using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.User inputs were validated using keypress events, input fields were dynamically highlighted on mouse hover,
and a confirmation message was displayed using a double-click event on the submit button. JavaScript functions were used to provide reusable and efficient validation logic.
